    <stitle>AIR COMPRESSOR: BENDIX TU-FLO 501 - CLEAN AND INSPECT - CONNECTING ROD BEARINGS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CONNECTING ROD BEARINGS</title>
        <para>Used (old) bearing inserts must be replaced. Connecting rod caps are not interchangeable. The locking
            slots of the connecting rod and cap should be positioned adjacent to each other. Clearance between the
            connecting journal and the connecting rod bearing must not be less than .0003 inch (.00762mm) or more than
            .0021 inch (.05334mm) after rebuilding.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
